The Ethnic Youth Leaders have berated the Ondo State Governor, Rotimi Akeredolu, Prof. Itse Sagay and Omoyele Sowore for attacking the Governor of Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN), Godwin Emefiele, over move to contest the 2023 presidential election. Condemning the attack on the CBN governor, the groups asked why they should single out Emefiele and keep mute over others. The Ethnic Youth Leaders specifically noted that the President of the African Development Bank, Akinwumi Adesina, who also purchased the presidential form, was not attacked by this group of persons. -Advertisement- Describing the attack on Emefiele as ethnic rage, the groups, in a statement by Alhaji Kabiru Yusuf, said, â€œWe have just witnessed a brazen display of ethnic bigotry from the likes of Governor Akeredolu, Professor Sagay, and Sowore, who have come out to openly attack the person of the CBN governor on hearing that form has been purchased for him.